- **Thucydides**, *The Peloponnesian War* — cited
  for the rising-power fear dynamic (note 15),
  paired with **R. Gilpin**, *War and Change in
  World Politics* (1981)
- **Bairoch**, "International Industrialization Levels
  from 1750 to 1980" — data source for relative
  industrial shares (notes 20, 23, 24)
- **"Correlates of War"** dataset (Inter-University
  Consortium, Univ. of Michigan) — military
  personnel and expenditure figures
- **C. Barnett**, *The Collapse of British Power* —
  cited on British relative decline
- **R.J.B. Bosworth**, *Italy, the Least of the Great
  Powers* — Italy's structural weakness as a
  great power; described with "thoroughly
  depressing" Italian military efficiency sources
- **W. W. Rostow**, *The World Economy, History
  and Prospect* — railway mileage data
- **W. H. Beasley**, *The Meiji Restoration* and
  **E. H. Norman**, *Japan's Emergence as a
  Modern State* — Japanese modernization
- **I. Nish**, *The Origin of the Russo-Japanese War*
  (1985) — Russo-Japanese War background
- **J. N. Westwood**, *Russia Against Japan, 1904–5*
  — described as best account of the conflict
- **A. J. Sherman**, "German-Jewish Bankers in World
  Politics: The Financing of the Russo-Japanese
  War" — Jacob Schiff's role in financing Japan
  against Russia (Leo Baeck Institute Yearbook,
  vol. 28, 1983)
- **A. Mitchell**, *The German Influence in France
  After 1870* and *Victors and Vanquished* —
  German structural impact on French institutions
  post-1870

